    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-14T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-14T03:00:00-05:00" n="185"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d185">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.00/5–1454: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Pakistan (<persName type="from"
                            >Emmerson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Karachi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-14T13:00:00+05:00"
                            >May 14, 1954—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>915. Acting <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_HICOM1">HICOM</gloss>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d185fn1">J. D. Murray.</note> states <gloss target="#t_GOP1"
                        >GOP</gloss> agreeable participate supervisory arrangement for Indochina on
                    condition all parties including Communists sign agreement. Pakistanis apparently
                    not averse contributing troops for such purpose.</p>
                <p>Murray also says <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> approached by <gloss
                        target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> on <gloss target="#t_SEATO1">SEATO</gloss> and
                    likewise favorably disposed although points out Pakistan Middle East
                    responsibilities at present lack military strength prevent sizeable contribution
                    SEA defense. Nevertheless position East Bengal denotes important Pakistan
                    interest SEA. Murray emphasized <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> policy is to
                    keep Indochina supervisory arrangement and <gloss target="#t_SEATO1"
                        >SEATO</gloss> entirely separate.</p>
                <p>Embassy assumes Department desires <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> carry ball,
                    endorses Delhi’s request information on US policy this matter (Delhi 1676 to
                        Department)<note n="2" xml:id="d185fn2">Not printed.</note> would be
                    especially helpful know Department attitude toward Pakistan role.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Emmerson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
